# CS 305 – Secure Software Development


### Client Summary and Software Requirements

Artemis Financial is a consulting company that develops personalized financial plans for its clients, including services related to savings, retirement, investments, and insurance. 
The company wanted to modernize its web-based application while ensuring that sensitive customer financial data was properly protected. The primary issue Artemis Financial asked Global 
Rain to address was identifying security vulnerabilities within their software and implementing secure coding practices to protect data integrity, confidentiality, and trust.

### Strengths in Identifying Vulnerabilities and the Importance of Secure Coding

One area I performed well in was systematically identifying software security vulnerabilities using industry-standard tools and best practices. Secure coding is essential because vulnerabilities
can expose sensitive data, damage customer trust, and create legal and financial risks for a company. Software security adds value by protecting company assets, ensuring regulatory compliance, and 
maintaining the organization’s reputation. Proactively addressing vulnerabilities reduces long-term costs and strengthens overall system reliability.

### Challenging and Helpful Aspects of the Vulnerability Assessment

The most challenging aspect of the vulnerability assessment was interpreting vulnerability reports and distinguishing true threats from false positives. However, this process was also one of the most
valuable learning experiences. It strengthened my understanding of how vulnerabilities are categorized, prioritized, and mitigated, and it reinforced the importance of careful analysis rather than blindly 
accepting automated scan results.

### Increasing Layers of Security and Future Assessment Methods

I increased layers of security by applying secure communication practices, using cryptographic hashing for data integrity, and refactoring code to follow secure development standards. In the future, I would
continue using tools such as OWASP Dependency-Check, static code analysis tools, and secure code reviews to assess vulnerabilities. I would also rely on threat modeling and risk-based analysis to determine 
which mitigation techniques provide the greatest security impact.

### Ensuring Functionality and Security After Refactoring

To ensure the application remained functional and secure after refactoring, I tested all application features to confirm expected behavior. I re-ran vulnerability scans and reviewed dependency reports to verify
that no new security issues were introduced. This validation process ensured that security improvements did not compromise application functionality or stability.

### Resources, Tools, and Practices for Future Use

Throughout this project, I used tools and practices that will continue to be valuable in future assignments and professional work, including OWASP Dependency-Check, secure coding standards, cryptographic hashing
techniques, and structured code reviews. These tools reinforced a DevSecOps mindset by integrating security throughout the development lifecycle rather than treating it as a final step.

### Artifacts for Future Employers

For future employers, I would showcase the completed Artemis Financial secure software report, along with supporting code examples and vulnerability assessment results. This assignment demonstrates my ability to
assess real-world security risks, apply secure coding techniques, and validate software functionality—skills that are critical for modern software development roles.
